This paper is about language modeling using Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge distillation and trust regularization, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second likely category. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques to improve the performance of RNNLMs, making cs.AI the third likely category. The paper also discusses the reduction of model size and computation, which falls under the category of software engineering and programming, making cs.SD (Software Engineering) the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of RNNLMs in speech recognition, which falls under the category of systems and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) the fifth likely category.
